<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-413-972  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 413 972.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  April 30 1990 v36 n1807 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Commerce seeks input on Randamp;D proposal. (U.S. Commerce DepartmentTechnology Administration, Advanced Technology Program)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Department of Commerce Technology Administration wantspublic comment on its proposed guidelines for the AdvancedTechnology Program (ATP).andP;  ATP is a $10 million research anddevelopment program to provide government funding to individualand groups of businesses.andP;  The program is administered by theNational Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) and theprojects are to lie within NIST's areas of expertise.andP;  No onecompany can receive more than $2 million in funding.andP;  The emphasisof the program is on 'pre-competitive generic technology.'andO;Criteria for the evaluation of proposals are technical andscientific merit, commercial benefit, technology transferbenefits, qualifications of the submitting business or group, thesubmitter's commitment and the submitting organization'sstructure.andP;  The guidelines also cover issuing of reports,licensing issues and intellectual property rights.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of Commerce. Technology Administration.andO;Government FundingResearch and DevelopmentUnited States. National Institute of Standards and Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>